<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3294/14–15.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Vignaud</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-07"><hi rend="italic">March 7,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 272.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of the
                            ambassador’s No. 234 of the 31st of January last, transmitting copy of
                            his note of January 23 to the minister for foreign affairs regarding the
                            arrest and imprisonment case of Frederick Lodge Jacobs.</p>
                        <p>The department approves Mr. McCormick’s note and awaits with interest the
                            embassy’s further report.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>